oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Odell Powell inspects corn
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Clement, William L., photographer
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Odell Powell is shown with outstanding corn crop on Dickson soil fertilized at the rate of six hundred pounds per acre of 6-12-12 fertilizer and two hundred pounds of ammonium nitrate. Corn was planted on contour and stripcropped. Located eight miles south of Woodbury.

One in a series of photographs of agricultural activities in Cannon County, TN that were taken by W.L. Clement, District Conservationist for the U.S. Soil Conservation Service, and his assistants between the mid-1940s and mid-1970s.
